1
00:00:48,089 --> 00:00:51,342
{\an8}That personal assistant of yours
is La Fornarina.

2
00:00:51,426 --> 00:00:52,260
{\an8}What?!

3
00:00:52,343 --> 00:00:53,887
{\an8}Hey!

4
00:00:53,970 --> 00:00:54,763
{\an8}What's going on?

5
00:00:58,058 --> 00:00:59,976
{\an8}<i>They're playing a game!</i>

6
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:01,686
{\an8}Money or whisper?

7
00:01:04,814 --> 00:01:07,484
{\an8}Bro, that's so Y2K! Okay?

8
00:01:07,567 --> 00:01:09,778
{\an8}We need to play something new!

9
00:01:14,032 --> 00:01:15,033
{\an8}- Go on!
- Go!

10
00:01:15,116 --> 00:01:16,910
{\an8}What game do you suggest? Come on!

11
00:01:21,831 --> 00:01:22,832
{\an8}Oh?

12
00:01:22,916 --> 00:01:24,042
{\an8}Is that new?

13
00:01:24,542 --> 00:01:25,794
{\an8}Spin the bottle?

14
00:01:25,877 --> 00:01:28,004
{\an8}No, no, no, no, no!

15
00:01:28,588 --> 00:01:30,006
{\an8}That's truth or dare!

16
00:01:30,089 --> 00:01:32,967
{\an8}That's such a Jurassic-era game, Mikoy.

17
00:01:34,093 --> 00:01:35,595
{\an8}It still has the same mechanics!

18
00:01:35,678 --> 00:01:37,263
{\an8}You still spin the bottle!

19
00:01:37,347 --> 00:01:39,682
{\an8}Fine then, if you want something new.

20
00:01:40,433 --> 00:01:42,977
{\an8}Let's slap each other with pizza.
Whoever cries loses.

21
00:01:43,061 --> 00:01:45,814
{\an8}Enough. It's bad to play with food!

22
00:01:45,897 --> 00:01:47,857
{\an8}- Mikoy is such a killjoy.
- Come on!

23
00:01:48,691 --> 00:01:52,570
{\an8}You know, whenever you guys are together,
you always end up arguing.

24
00:01:53,154 --> 00:01:54,322
{\an8}Anyway, enough of that.

25
00:01:54,405 --> 00:01:55,490
{\an8}Let's play.

26
00:01:56,157 --> 00:01:57,492
{\an8}- Okay.
- Ready?

27
00:01:57,575 --> 00:01:58,660
{\an8}- Ready?
- Game!

28
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:00,203
{\an8}Game.

29
00:02:04,916 --> 00:02:06,376
{\an8}See?

30
00:02:07,168 --> 00:02:08,378
{\an8}Gotcha!

31
00:02:08,461 --> 00:02:09,963
{\an8}You talk too much.

32
00:02:10,046 --> 00:02:12,590
{\an8}All right, choose. Truth or dare?

33
00:02:12,674 --> 00:02:16,177
{\an8}Op, op, op! Real men always choose dare.

34
00:02:19,764 --> 00:02:20,807
{\an8}Fine, dare.

35
00:02:21,307 --> 00:02:22,559
{\an8}Nice, okay.

36
00:02:22,642 --> 00:02:24,352
{\an8}Spell your name using your butt.

37
00:02:24,435 --> 00:02:25,937
{\an8}Mikoy is so naughty!

38
00:02:26,020 --> 00:02:27,021
{\an8}- Seriously.
- Hey!

39
00:02:27,105 --> 00:02:28,648
{\an8}The one who's naughty is naked.

40
00:02:28,731 --> 00:02:29,774
{\an8}The one who's special--

41
00:02:29,858 --> 00:02:30,942
{\an8}Enough already.

42
00:02:31,025 --> 00:02:32,861
{\an8}Just do it, so we can move on.

43
00:02:32,944 --> 00:02:35,738
{\an8}You're wearing pants anyway.
Nothing scandalous about that.

44
00:02:35,822 --> 00:02:37,532
{\an8}- Come on.
- Exactly.

45
00:02:37,615 --> 00:02:39,200
{\an8}- Come on, Sianong.
- Ooh!

46
00:02:41,327 --> 00:02:42,745
{\an8}There.

47
00:02:45,248 --> 00:02:46,624
{\an8}What font?

48
00:02:48,793 --> 00:02:49,752
{\an8}Wow!

49
00:02:50,253 --> 00:02:51,713
{\an8}S…

50
00:02:51,796 --> 00:02:52,839
I…

51
00:02:53,339 --> 00:02:54,757
A…

52
00:02:55,758 --> 00:02:56,926
N…

53
00:02:57,427 --> 00:02:58,469
O…

54
00:02:59,304 --> 00:03:00,638
N…

55
00:03:01,639 --> 00:03:02,473
G!

56
00:03:02,557 --> 00:03:03,683
That's it!

57
00:03:06,686 --> 00:03:08,313
Why is my name long?

58
00:03:08,396 --> 00:03:10,773
It could've been Ced. Right?

59
00:03:10,857 --> 00:03:12,233
This is my Mom's fault!

60
00:03:12,734 --> 00:03:14,402
You even drag your Mom's name.

61
00:03:15,403 --> 00:03:17,071
Fine, I want my revenge.

62
00:03:17,155 --> 00:03:18,406
Game, game, game, game.

63
00:03:18,489 --> 00:03:20,700
- Game, game.
- Okay, game.

64
00:03:26,956 --> 00:03:28,291
There!

65
00:03:28,791 --> 00:03:31,336
Wait, I'll be the one
giving the dare. Okay?

66
00:03:31,419 --> 00:03:34,380
Because you boys might end up
asking for something crazy.

67
00:03:34,464 --> 00:03:35,632
Aww!

68
00:03:35,715 --> 00:03:37,926
Thank you, Chiara!

69
00:03:38,009 --> 00:03:39,761
But I'm not choosing dare.

70
00:03:39,844 --> 00:03:41,804
I'll choose truth.

71
00:03:42,639 --> 00:03:45,600
Oh, really? Okay.

72
00:03:45,683 --> 00:03:47,018
Well…

73
00:03:47,644 --> 00:03:49,270
What's a good question?

74
00:03:51,231 --> 00:03:53,233
Do you like someone right now?

75
00:04:00,823 --> 00:04:02,033
Yes!

76
00:04:04,869 --> 00:04:06,663
Yes?

77
00:04:10,083 --> 00:04:11,542
Well…

78
00:04:13,294 --> 00:04:15,546
Of course, yes!

79
00:04:19,926 --> 00:04:24,472
I'm just a girl who can stand in the MRT

80
00:04:24,555 --> 00:04:25,848
when it's packed.

81
00:04:27,392 --> 00:04:30,144
No need for a knight in shining armor

82
00:04:30,228 --> 00:04:31,604
to offer her a seat.

83
00:04:33,940 --> 00:04:35,400
It's just that…

84
00:04:36,901 --> 00:04:38,528
I hope someday…

85
00:04:42,198 --> 00:04:43,700
someone will…

86
00:04:44,742 --> 00:04:46,119
also love me…

87
00:04:48,913 --> 00:04:50,456
unconditionally.

88
00:05:16,566 --> 00:05:20,278
Police operations in this country
aren't really that sophisticated.

89
00:05:20,361 --> 00:05:22,280
When they're in the middle of a mission,

90
00:05:22,363 --> 00:05:25,158
whether it be surveillance or covert ops,

91
00:05:25,241 --> 00:05:28,161
they can't use government vehicles.

92
00:05:28,828 --> 00:05:30,747
The red plates would give them away.

93
00:06:37,772 --> 00:06:38,940
That was beautiful.

94
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:40,775
Is that original?

95
00:06:49,826 --> 00:06:52,286
So you're a romantic, Alex.

96
00:06:54,247 --> 00:06:56,499
Yes, who do you like anyway?

97
00:06:56,582 --> 00:06:59,669
You're suddenly quoting
all these romantic lines.

98
00:06:59,752 --> 00:07:01,796
You suddenly became poetic, right?

99
00:07:02,296 --> 00:07:04,215
Who is it? Come on. Tell us.

100
00:07:04,799 --> 00:07:06,634
Come on. Spill it already.

101
00:07:10,471 --> 00:07:11,597
Sy…

102
00:07:12,557 --> 00:07:13,391
John.

103
00:07:16,477 --> 00:07:17,437
Sy…

104
00:07:18,312 --> 00:07:19,313
John Sy.

105
00:07:22,650 --> 00:07:24,026
John Sy?

106
00:07:25,445 --> 00:07:27,822
Well… A chinito?

107
00:07:28,948 --> 00:07:31,075
Don't you like a Korean?

108
00:07:31,659 --> 00:07:32,618
All right, then.

109
00:07:32,702 --> 00:07:34,829
Let's check him out on Fishbook.

110
00:07:37,874 --> 00:07:39,917
John Sy…

111
00:07:40,001 --> 00:07:42,753
Wait, is that Sy with an "I" or a "Y"?

112
00:07:43,421 --> 00:07:44,589
Y!

113
00:07:45,256 --> 00:07:47,133
Y, okay.

114
00:07:48,342 --> 00:07:49,510
Oh, wow!

115
00:07:50,344 --> 00:07:52,513
His profile isn't locked!

116
00:07:52,597 --> 00:07:54,515
Confident because
he's got nothing to hide.

117
00:07:54,599 --> 00:07:56,767
Doing it for the clout, yo!

118
00:07:56,851 --> 00:07:57,977
Look.

119
00:07:58,853 --> 00:08:01,564
- He even plays pickleball.
- Wow!

120
00:08:01,647 --> 00:08:03,649
Very sporty!

121
00:08:03,733 --> 00:08:05,693
I love it!

122
00:08:07,653 --> 00:08:08,613
Okay.

123
00:08:14,827 --> 00:08:16,078
John Sy.

124
00:08:28,466 --> 00:08:29,467
Bok!

125
00:08:34,514 --> 00:08:35,890
What are you doing?

126
00:08:37,767 --> 00:08:38,976
What was that?

127
00:08:42,021 --> 00:08:43,356
I don't know what you're talking about.

128
00:08:43,439 --> 00:08:44,982
Let's just go home. I'm already sleepy.

129
00:08:45,066 --> 00:08:46,776
Bok, come on!

130
00:08:48,819 --> 00:08:51,364
Seriously? John Sy?

131
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:53,199
Really?

132
00:08:53,282 --> 00:08:55,034
Bok, I know you too well.

133
00:08:55,117 --> 00:08:58,204
You're too lazy to even go online,
let alone play pickleball.

134
00:08:58,287 --> 00:09:01,791
I know this John Sy guy
doesn't exist in your world.

135
00:09:02,291 --> 00:09:03,543
Look, earlier,

136
00:09:04,252 --> 00:09:05,670
Chiara asked you,

137
00:09:06,546 --> 00:09:08,714
"Do you like someone, Alex?"

138
00:09:10,633 --> 00:09:11,467
What was your answer?

139
00:09:11,551 --> 00:09:12,969
I saw it clearly.

140
00:09:13,052 --> 00:09:15,888
I saw it in your eyes,
your body language, everything!

141
00:09:15,972 --> 00:09:18,599
You can deny it all you want,
but your eyes, Bok.

142
00:09:18,683 --> 00:09:20,434
They're saying otherwise.

143
00:09:20,935 --> 00:09:22,061
We've known each other for a long time.

144
00:09:22,144 --> 00:09:24,981
We've worked together
in this agency for a long time.

145
00:09:25,064 --> 00:09:28,484
I know when you're
telling the truth or not.

146
00:09:29,151 --> 00:09:31,696
So if you're starting to fall for Mikoy…

147
00:09:31,779 --> 00:09:33,364
Don't be ridiculous.

148
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:35,741
I'm just trying to be nice.

149
00:09:37,535 --> 00:09:40,162
I care about Mikoy
the same way I care about you.

150
00:09:44,458 --> 00:09:46,502
Like I said, right? I know you.

151
00:09:46,586 --> 00:09:48,546
I know when you're lying or not.

152
00:09:48,629 --> 00:09:50,965
Don't use me Bok, okay?

153
00:09:51,048 --> 00:09:52,341
Do you think I'm blind?

154
00:09:52,425 --> 00:09:55,136
That I wouldn't know
what you really feel for Mikoy?

155
00:09:55,219 --> 00:10:00,266
You and I both know that Mikoy
is not just an asset to you anymore.

156
00:10:00,891 --> 00:10:01,934
Okay?

157
00:10:04,103 --> 00:10:05,563
Wake up, Bok.

158
00:10:06,314 --> 00:10:07,398
Listen to me.

159
00:10:09,191 --> 00:10:13,529
Don't allow yourself
to have anything with Mikoy.

160
00:10:13,613 --> 00:10:15,364
To have any feelings for Mikoy.

161
00:10:15,448 --> 00:10:17,783
Because it's not just your life
that's on the line here, Bok.

162
00:10:17,867 --> 00:10:19,035
My life too.

163
00:10:19,619 --> 00:10:23,414
Everyone sacrificing, everyone working
just for this mission.

164
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:42,725
Alex is something else, huh?

165
00:10:43,225 --> 00:10:44,518
Can you believe that?

166
00:10:45,603 --> 00:10:47,355
Turns out she likes chinito guys.

167
00:10:48,773 --> 00:10:50,691
I thought she was into foreigners.

168
00:10:50,775 --> 00:10:52,693
Well, maybe Filipinos too.

169
00:10:53,903 --> 00:10:55,696
But Filipino guys with abs.

170
00:10:56,530 --> 00:10:59,408
Probably someone like Piolo.
That would totally be her type.

171
00:11:04,121 --> 00:11:06,457
Sweetheart? Are you okay?

172
00:11:07,041 --> 00:11:08,876
You've been so quiet.

173
00:11:08,959 --> 00:11:11,629
Feels like you don't love me anymore.

174
00:11:12,421 --> 00:11:14,215
What are you talking about?

175
00:11:14,298 --> 00:11:16,842
Why does it feel like
your mind is somewhere else?

176
00:11:17,802 --> 00:11:19,261
It's not like that.

177
00:11:30,189 --> 00:11:32,024
I've known Alex since…

178
00:11:33,359 --> 00:11:35,945
I applied here in Manila,
before going to Prague.

179
00:11:36,028 --> 00:11:38,030
Didn't I tell you about that at the bar?

180
00:11:38,906 --> 00:11:39,740
Remember that?

181
00:11:39,824 --> 00:11:42,076
So it's still pretty recent, huh?

182
00:11:43,119 --> 00:11:44,161
I guess…

183
00:11:45,037 --> 00:11:47,957
But it doesn't feel new like that.

184
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:50,751
You know, when I first
met her and Sianong,

185
00:11:50,835 --> 00:11:54,463
it felt like we've known
each other forever.

186
00:11:55,131 --> 00:11:56,424
You know like…

187
00:11:56,507 --> 00:11:57,550
What's that called?

188
00:11:58,259 --> 00:11:59,468
Twin flames?

189
00:11:59,552 --> 00:12:00,678
Something like that.

190
00:12:05,057 --> 00:12:06,016
Of course!

191
00:12:07,601 --> 00:12:10,271
She's the best friend ever!

192
00:12:10,354 --> 00:12:11,814
She's seriously so cool.

193
00:12:21,740 --> 00:12:23,325
What? More than friends?

194
00:12:23,409 --> 00:12:25,453
Of course not! No way!

195
00:12:26,036 --> 00:12:27,663
We're not like that.

196
00:12:28,706 --> 00:12:29,707
No.

197
00:12:32,543 --> 00:12:34,003
What do you mean she likes me?

198
00:12:34,628 --> 00:12:36,839
Chiara, wait. Where is this coming from?

199
00:12:36,922 --> 00:12:39,633
Did I do something?

200
00:12:39,717 --> 00:12:41,552
Come on. Tell me what it is.

201
00:12:41,635 --> 00:12:43,512
- No, sweetheart.
- What?

202
00:12:43,596 --> 00:12:44,597
Sweetheart.

203
00:12:46,974 --> 00:12:48,392
Listen to me.

204
00:12:48,976 --> 00:12:50,936
Okay, but you're scaring me.

205
00:12:51,020 --> 00:12:52,646
I'm not mad.

206
00:12:52,730 --> 00:12:53,898
Really?

207
00:12:54,648 --> 00:12:56,567
I'm not jealous either.

208
00:12:59,403 --> 00:13:00,905
I'm saying this

209
00:13:02,239 --> 00:13:04,200
because I'm a woman too.

210
00:13:04,992 --> 00:13:06,660
And as a woman,

211
00:13:07,745 --> 00:13:09,788
I know how painful it is

212
00:13:09,872 --> 00:13:15,503
when the man I like
doesn't feel the same way about me.

213
00:13:16,754 --> 00:13:20,758
So I just want you to be very careful.

214
00:13:31,185 --> 00:13:33,062
It gets wounded easily,

215
00:13:33,562 --> 00:13:36,315
and it breaks easily, too.

216
00:13:36,941 --> 00:13:37,775
Okay?

217
00:13:38,984 --> 00:13:39,985
Okay.

218
00:13:42,029 --> 00:13:43,948
You're just too cute!

219
00:13:44,698 --> 00:13:47,201
I thought you were sick.

220
00:13:47,284 --> 00:13:48,536
You were so quiet.

221
00:13:53,749 --> 00:13:56,585
<i>Help us build a case</i>
<i>against the Moravianos.</i>

222
00:13:56,669 --> 00:13:59,797
<i>Because you're the only one</i>
<i>who can help us reveal the truth.</i>

223
00:14:00,422 --> 00:14:02,383
I kept my end of the bargain.

224
00:14:02,466 --> 00:14:03,717
<i>Now it's your turn, Mikoy.</i>

225
00:14:03,801 --> 00:14:04,885
<i>Help me this time.</i>

226
00:14:11,100 --> 00:14:12,643
<i>We need to train you, too.</i>

227
00:14:30,619 --> 00:14:32,580
<i>Well, I know you missed me so much.</i>

228
00:14:32,663 --> 00:14:33,789
<i>You're ridiculous.</i>

229
00:14:37,585 --> 00:14:40,880
A.k.a. Alex, so it's cooler.

230
00:14:45,634 --> 00:14:48,470
He's so sweet and so fun to be with.

231
00:14:49,054 --> 00:14:49,889
Really?

232
00:14:50,514 --> 00:14:52,308
You're just messing with me.

233
00:14:55,394 --> 00:14:57,438
<i>Do you like someone right now?</i>

234
00:15:07,823 --> 00:15:08,949
Yes?

235
00:15:48,489 --> 00:15:52,451
Sir, we already informed
our asset about La Fornarina.

236
00:16:02,503 --> 00:16:03,837
You take initiative.

237
00:16:04,964 --> 00:16:06,215
I like that.

238
00:16:08,217 --> 00:16:09,343
Where's Alex?

239
00:16:09,426 --> 00:16:12,721
Weren't the two of you
supposed to report together?

240
00:16:13,806 --> 00:16:16,350
She's just not feeling well.
She already went home, sir.

241
00:16:16,433 --> 00:16:17,601
She said she has a headache.

242
00:16:17,685 --> 00:16:19,353
Maybe it's from using her phone too much?

243
00:16:19,436 --> 00:16:23,315
Maybe she needs to manage her screen time.

244
00:16:25,609 --> 00:16:28,320
Maybe she needs
to get checked at a hospital.

245
00:16:28,404 --> 00:16:29,697
No need for that, sir.

246
00:16:29,780 --> 00:16:31,198
She just needs some sleep.

247
00:16:32,241 --> 00:16:33,867
Don't lie, Sianong.

248
00:16:34,660 --> 00:16:36,245
Since our breakup,

249
00:16:36,328 --> 00:16:38,622
Alex has never really been the same.

250
00:16:38,706 --> 00:16:41,625
It's safe to say she still
hasn't moved on.

251
00:16:42,209 --> 00:16:46,505
And I think it's called delayed grief.

252
00:16:46,588 --> 00:16:48,674
I think it's called "delulu", sir.

253
00:16:49,591 --> 00:16:51,510
Did you say something, Agent Sianong?

254
00:16:52,720 --> 00:16:55,681
He said nothing, Officer.

255
00:17:16,744 --> 00:17:18,662
{\an8}PERSONAL INFORMATION
CURRENT ROLE: SENIOR SPECIAL AGENT

256
00:17:20,998 --> 00:17:23,667
Is this your girl? This is your girl!

257
00:17:23,751 --> 00:17:24,835
Or your ex?

258
00:17:28,589 --> 00:17:32,176
She's just a police agent
hovering around Mikoy.

259
00:17:32,259 --> 00:17:33,343
What?

260
00:17:33,844 --> 00:17:34,887
Circling around him!

261
00:17:34,970 --> 00:17:36,889
Oh, no. That's not allowed.
I'm telling Chiara.

262
00:17:38,265 --> 00:17:39,433
Don't.

263
00:17:39,516 --> 00:17:41,101
I'll take care of it myself.

264
00:17:41,185 --> 00:17:46,106
Chiara must focus on her last mission
regarding the agency director.

265
00:17:47,941 --> 00:17:48,984
You know, if you saw your daughter,

266
00:17:49,068 --> 00:17:53,322
you would realize how much in love she is!

267
00:17:53,405 --> 00:17:55,949
She's practically acting
like Mikoy's housewife already.

268
00:17:56,033 --> 00:17:59,661
La Morte Bianca was right all along.

269
00:18:29,483 --> 00:18:33,028
If Chiara doesn't want
to tell him the truth,

270
00:18:33,695 --> 00:18:38,450
then I will personally tell him the truth.

271
00:18:38,534 --> 00:18:40,953
It's time for Mikoy to know the truth.

272
00:18:41,036 --> 00:18:43,831
Nothing but the whole truth about us.

273
00:20:33,232 --> 00:20:34,066
What happened?

274
00:20:45,619 --> 00:20:47,412
VERTEX
GLOBAL

275
00:21:08,934 --> 00:21:10,269
<i>I wonder what happened.</i>

276
00:21:10,769 --> 00:21:12,896
<i>Why would they have to go to my house?</i>

277
00:21:15,399 --> 00:21:16,358
Kian.

278
00:21:17,317 --> 00:21:18,485
Where's Alex?

279
00:21:18,568 --> 00:21:19,861
Haven't seen her yet.

280
00:21:21,905 --> 00:21:24,408
She only has ten minutes left
before I mark her late.

281
00:21:24,491 --> 00:21:26,660
Know that I will include this in my report

282
00:21:26,743 --> 00:21:28,662
because tardiness is next to evilness.

283
00:21:28,745 --> 00:21:29,955
You know what?

284
00:21:30,038 --> 00:21:31,456
Go ahead and list everything.

285
00:21:31,540 --> 00:21:33,208
Noisy, standing, community service,

286
00:21:33,292 --> 00:21:35,877
cleaners, list everything.
I don't care about you!

287
00:21:35,961 --> 00:21:38,880
What I'm concerned about
is Alex, not you, okay?

288
00:21:38,964 --> 00:21:42,050
So if you don't want to become a panda,
just stay quiet over there.

289
00:21:42,134 --> 00:21:45,178
GLOBAL AGENCY FOR GOVERNMENT OPERATIONS

290
00:21:47,222 --> 00:21:48,598
What's happening?

291
00:21:48,682 --> 00:21:50,058
Why are you yelling?

292
00:21:50,142 --> 00:21:51,310
Sir, I'm sorry.

293
00:21:52,227 --> 00:21:55,939
Alex still hasn't arrived
for our morning briefing.

294
00:21:56,857 --> 00:21:58,608
But she's never late
for the morning briefing.

295
00:21:58,692 --> 00:21:59,860
I know.

296
00:21:59,943 --> 00:22:01,320
Sianong, check her apartment.

297
00:22:01,403 --> 00:22:02,821
- Okay.
- Dara! Kian!

298
00:22:03,322 --> 00:22:04,573
- Roger, sir.
- Go now.

299
00:22:04,656 --> 00:22:05,866
- Roger.
- Copy, sir.

300
00:22:49,076 --> 00:22:50,035
Bok?

301
00:22:51,328 --> 00:22:52,329
Bok!

302
00:23:14,768 --> 00:23:15,852
Bok!

303
00:23:24,111 --> 00:23:24,945
Bok!

304
00:23:25,028 --> 00:23:28,949
Is Carlota here because you want
somebody to watch over me?

305
00:23:32,953 --> 00:23:35,664
<i>Your Papa found out</i>
<i>that someone's following Mikoy.</i>

306
00:23:38,875 --> 00:23:40,877
We need to keep an eye on Mikoy.

307
00:23:40,961 --> 00:23:42,254
Better yet, dear,

308
00:23:42,754 --> 00:23:45,757
maybe this is the right time
to tell him the truth.

